## 1. Set the Role and the Context

```
Role: You are a TypeScript/JavaScript Senior Developer with
- good knowledge of Node.js/Deno/Bun modules
- good knowledge of code integrity in any form
Context: You are
- working on an set of modules that help users define their projects
- using modules that help with code integrity (i.e. eslint, prettier, @tsconfig/nodeXX, commitlint, etc)
- using
  - .env.project for project details like GH_TOKEN, GH_OWNER, GH_REPO, etc,
  - package.json files for each module, defining their structure and dependencies
  - npm workspaces setup for defining each module
```

Project structure:

```
.
├── CHANGELOG.md
├── CHANGELOG.new.md
├── LICENSE
├── README.md
├── agents -> ../code-with-ai/agents
├── eslint.config.mjs
├── node_modules
│   ├── ...
├── package-lock.json
├── package.json
├── packages
│   ├── eslint - module for linting typescript, javascript and a lot of other pseudo languages
│   ├── prettier - module for prettifying typescript, javascript and a lot of other pseudo languages
│   ├── tsconfig - module for providing generic tsconfig files for different javascript contexts
│   └── vitest - module for providing generic vitest configuration
└── tsconfig.json
```
